Native to the Atlantic and Gulf coasts of North America from Newfoundland and Labrador, Canada, to Texas, U.S.A. ( Mobberley 1956 , Barkworth 2003 ), and Tamaulipas and Veracruz, Mexico (
Mora-Olivo and Valdes-Reyna 2011
). Introduced in England, France, and Spain ( Campos et al. 2004 ), the west coast of the United States (Washington, Oregon, California), New Zealand ( Partridge 1987 ), and China ( Bixing and Phillips 2006 , An et al. 2007 , Scholz et al. 2009 ).
